glyphic inscriptions. Highlighting such previously overlooked topics as sexuality and generational struggles, this beautifully illustrated book paves the way for a new understanding of Maya myths and their lavish expression in ancient art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Apr 2020) 7aART / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224672423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300224672.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles